WASHINGTON, November 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in leading U.S. newspapers today: The Washington Post: -- The U.S. National Institutes of Health yesterday concluded for the first time that the ancient Chinese art of acupuncture is an effective treatment for certain kinds of pain and nausea and shows promise for a variety of other conditions, providing an unprecedented endorsement by the Western medical establishment. The Wall Street Journal: -- Some Wall Street economists cut estimates for 1998 economic growth by 0.5 percentage point or more, because of the turmoil in Southeast Asia but also due to some domestic concerns. The New York Times: -- Iraq is using the cover of negotiations to hide evidence about its arms programs, the chief investigator for the United Nations said.